caption: Caribella is one of my favorite local breakfast & lunch spots. Everyone that works at Caribella is so friendly and welcoming. Great variety of food options with great prices. The iced coquito latte is my all time favorite ❤️
I love this place. It was lowkey and romantic. Great atmosphere for couples. The food is amazing. Our waiter was fantastic.
Amazing food and service.
Excellent place food was so good I drove from, Milwaukee just to try and I wasn't disappointed.  Worth the drive!
You just cannot go wrong with this place! They are very friendly and the food is absolutely amazing! The pancakes 🥞 and skillets are delicious!

Top-notch Restaurant! There are very satisfying and inexpensive dishes available at this cozy restaurant. As they were so friendly and accessible, I thanked their staves. When our food was quickly delivered, I was so shocked. All of their dishes are perfect! Among the rest, the best guys are you! A very nice recommendation!
I wish I could give this place more stars!! The most AMAZING food, WONDERFUL staff and the service is the very BEST!!

Awesome shop for coffee! My husband and I were given the chance to discuss what we need for the future. This coffee shop environment was a huge help. With their silent and green décor, they were impressive. It makes us feel they weren't in town, refreshing in the garden somewhere. Many thanks to the helpful staff who welcomed us. Nice way! Fair way! Good way!
Staff welcoming, very nice and professional.
Went there for a birthday celebration. Great service. Great food.
Absolutely loved my experience! Excellent customer service and the food is delicious
Amazing quality sushi. Staff was friendly and attentive
Everything was delicious and super fresh! It's a great place to go to celebrate a special occasion.
Stunning view and amazing staff! It was such a lovely meal and we felt so well looked after. Would highly recommend it for a special occasion!

Wow.  This place puts out some Amazing Dishes.   Spouse found this place and wanted to try so we walked over for lunch and got a little table outside.   The menu is small and straightforward.  A wonderful cafe that has a perfect cafe feeling where as the food and drinks have a great Caribbean feeling.   The service was fantastic.   The food omg was it amazing.   The Puerto Rican Rice (Arroz Con Gandules) was amazeballs.  The Cubano is one of the best I have had in the states.   The table next to us ordered the Frittata  and the smells of peppers and great spices invaded our area.  I will for sure try this one soon.
i love how strong their coffee is. one of the best coffee i've tasted. they also serve good food
The food is always delicious.  The staff were friendly and efficient.
Loved it, can't wait to be back in Chicago just to have more.

We tried this restaurant, and it was worth it. It was very phenomenal from food to its facilities. My boyfriend and I have enjoyed our time here. It's just a great restaurant that we're sure to recommend to everyone out there. Nice jobs, everybody. Keep it up, man!
Great management staff and bartenders are the greatest and always know what you are drinking.
Fantastic!  Burgers cooked to order, amazing sweet potato fries, and gigantic fresh made onion rings.
If you love burgers, this is seriously a place you need to try!!
Great lunch experience. Service was great, food was fantastic, and prices are very fair.
The atmosphere feels good.  The food is always delicious.  The staff were friendly and efficient.

My favorite restaurant in CARIBELLA! They have an awesome happy hour for wine and food, and all the different style/flavors of their CARIBELLA are so delicious! Go with the half size so you can order more flavors.

The waitress serving our food was very nice and very helpful. Surely, this restaurant will satisfy your cravings. They will not fulfill your food and service standards. Thanks for the delicious lunch!

The staff was very friendly and engaged in conversation with all of the customers while they waited for their food and drinks. The building was clean and well-kept and had beautiful artwork displayed inside and out.  Highly recommended!
The avocado club is super delicious!

I really like their food, shakes, and serving. The service is consistent and I really enjoyed it, perhaps it was the reason why I get coming back to this restaurant in the future. If you are looking for a fantastic dinner, look no further, try this restaurant. Thank you!
Tasty food.

No doubt that this coffee shop is well-known because of its coffee and pastries are the best here. I'm so fortunate that I was able to try it and it was nice because everything here is amazing and satisfying. Also, the service is outstanding, and I like to recommend these guys for that!

My husband and I came here for the first time. The breakfast portions were perfect and very delicious. They sell coquito lattes, coquito, and coquito french toast. They make their own syrup for the french toast with rum. You can tell they make most of their food from scratch and on the spot. The wait was a little long, but it was worth it. The outdoor seating is limited, and there are no fire pits. So, if you plan to dine outside, please wear layers, as the weather is getting colder day by day. The waiter was very friendly too. This is a breakfast spot everyone must try!
Very, very delicious
Great coffe and the steak sandwich was really good

We ordered two breakfast sandwiches, guava pancakes and passion fruit juice. Incredible. The pancakes were perfect and I wish we would’ve ordered more! The restaurant is super clean and following all covid-19 regulations. Can’t wait to order again!

I had a really great breakfast there the other day. The server was nice, coquito french toast was amazing! My only concern is that the 2 cooks weren't wearing masks at all while working. Whether it's just for takeout or dining outside , that runs a risk not just to their servers and customers but to contaminating food during. Please have the cooks wear masks. Other than that I love this place
Friendly service, really great coffee and the food is A++. Will be going back!

I've been getting takeout from here almost every weekend for months now - the food is always consistently delicious and the service is always great! You can't really go wrong with anything on the menu, but my favorites are the avocado club, guava french toast, and the chorizo skillet.
The steak and cheese sandwich has been my favorite here for years... never disappoints!!
Every time I come here the food is great, both breakfast and lunch. They are a little slow on prep but the food is always fresh, hot, and worth the wait

I LOVE THIS PLACE! Their breakfast sandwiches are the best I’ve ever had. Food is always fresh and flavorful. Never can go wrong. I only wish they weren’t listed as “unavailable” so much on Ubereats since that’s what I usually use to order from them when I can’t make it in.
Everything here was absolutely delicious! Will definitely be coming back 😋
Great food, great people!

This place is a hidden gem. It's small and cozy. I went for breakfast on a Sunday morning. There was a 25 minute wait for a table then another 20 minute wait for the food to come. Well worth the wait. The swirl of flavor and freshness of the food was amazing. I definitely will return but on a different day and time when it's not so busy. 👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Very good
Delicious brunch, and mimosas. So many different options and they're all so delicious it so hard to decide once it comes down to ordering.

Had the plantains, french toast and their signature latte. The signature latte is delicious- horchata on crack haha, very sweet. Plantains were great, I got the sweet ones. I wish I had asked for sour cream. French toast was amazing. There was a bit of a wait in comparison to some places but not bad at all and the food is worth it. They are also very safe and have a nice sidewalk spot.

Food was amazing and the staff was friendly. I ordered the Banana, Chocolate Chip French Toast. It took a while to get my food but the place was busy and it ended up being worth the wait. Would highly recommend if you're in the neighborhood.
The best non-dairy French toast I have had. Made with coconut milk and coconut flakes
Great quality food great service
If you want a special dinning experience, this is the place. Amazing food, great team working in the kitchen and front of house. Very welcoming.
Though it is outdoor dining the service and food was excellent. I totally recommend this place to everyone.

This is my favorite spot around Chicago to study and just chill, their coffee is really good I usually ask the barista for their specials and ask for their recommendations and I have never been disappointed, it has some quiet area so I come here to read a book or just study. They have big couches and a lot of room for people to sit and chill
Wow... it was way better than I expected. A little sweet for my taste but otherwise completely amazing! The cream they put on top of the latte is heavenly. Will definitely be coming back here!
Great locally-owned brunch spot in the Logan Square neighborhood. They have a wide variety of options on their menu and their take-out is typically ready very quickly.

My husband and I ordered take out from Caribella today and loved everything we ordered. I got the Caribella skillet which has fried plantains--yum! We also ordered the guava pancakes and the coquito french toast. The flavor in the guava pancakes was delightful. I'm not normally a pancake fan, but they caught my eye. So glad we ordered them because they were our favorite.  They allowed us to pay over the phone and had a really great pickup system. Definitely will order from here again, and can't wait to try dining in person when it's possible again!

So delicious! Worth every penny! Had the caribella skillet and Coquito Latte it was so good. Ordered a side of fruit for my daughter and the presentation was beautiful. Also had the platano wrapped in bacon soooooo good. Also service was great and friendly.
I been a regular at this place for years, even before they change name (cafe bella) The food it's been really good consistently that's why I keep coming back.
Nice little brunch gem that nobody seems to know about. They ran out of chicken but they gave me free pancakes so I like them. Pretty presentation as well.

I absolutely love Caribella! It's truly one of my favorite places to visit. Today I had the pleasure of returning with my husband. We ordered my favorite Caribella Skillet with sweet plantains in it. My husband ordered with Mozzarella and I with cheddar cheese. To drink we got their specialty coffee: the COQUITO LATTE 🥰❤😍 Its Amazing! It's what made me return to coffee a year ago after being coffee free for a year and a half. We also started with the bacon wrapped plantains for our appetizer. The staff has always been very friendly and welcoming. The environment if filled with great Caribbean art and a very modern appeal. I highly recommend this and will always do so. I thank my best friend and the owner for supplying a gift certificate for a new experience!

Very good Fusion food. The coquito latte is not to be missed. My friend had the coquito french toast and that was amazing. I had a frittata, which took over 20 minutes (does say that on the menu). I was pretty disappointed and considering the wait time was expecting something pretty spectacular. I'll definitely be going back to try many other items. I'm not discouraged by the weight or quality of the frittata. That coquito latte is enough to keep me a customer!
Was taken care of right away with warm friendly faces. Simple food with a home feel to it.
Excellent breakfast, perfectly seasoned and cooked plantains!

Proudly family owned and managed by mother and daughter, this small secret spot is hidden on clear view. BYOB makes it perfect for mimosas and gatherings.  Brunch or to go the flavors are surprisingly pleasant.  Coffee and tea with a twist. Vegan friendly and willing to please. Must stop if you are in town! Caribella Caribbean fusion awesomeness!

Oh my! Yes first impressions are everything. I had the Caribbean chicken sandwich with side of rice. I knew from my first bite of rice that this would be good. Rice was savory, smooth, and so flavorful. Chicken sandwich was also excellent. Chicken tender and moist. Jerk spice was the best I can recall. Avocado was so fresh, creamy, and flavorful as well. Finally, the bread was fresh baked and undoubtedly the right bread for this sandwich. Service was delightful too!
Delicious foodnin a cute atmosphere with great service. 5/5, would dine there again!
I tried to get Sat dinner reservations but they were booked up until the next month so I went for Sunday brunch instead.
Great mix of food.
This place is awesome. You want good food? Come to caribella.
The coquito French toast are awesome.
The vegetarian Plaintain sandwich was delicious
This is a fantastic place for breakfast!  I love it!!
Delicious food and lattes!! Highly recommend
Very nice environment for eat and have a good conversation and good food Thank you for the waitress that the Beauty of The Place 🌈✝️🛐🎶🎃🎶
Good people,service and policenter place
Great brunch spot! Good food and friendly staff.
Great taste
Food was fantastic and great price. would recommend.
Really good coffee and food. The service was awesome
I come here all the time with my girlfriend and we love getting the skillet. Definitely a gem! Keep up the good work. The food is great
Amazing breakfast, excellent service.
Friendly staff and atmosphere was enjoyable. Food was also delicious! Will definitely go back!
Great little meet-up. Yummy breakfast and lunch. I was surprised to really like the platano hash browns 😋
Food was great!

I'm from the south side of Chicago but came to the north side to get my car repaired and I just thought it would be a good time to eat breakfast and stumbled on this brunch Cafe. Let me tell you, best decision this morning! It's an intimate setting but you don't need company to enjoy. The staff is so friendly and the food is top notch.
I am so en amorado of this place! The Caribella skillet is amazing as well as as the Coquito latte! Need to bring the whole family!
Great food and service
Probably best Philly I've had . Great food. Great service

Delicious food, cute outdoor seating!  Ordered churrasco and tostones, delicious! Ordered a deconstructed mofongo with shrimp, flavorful and garlicky! Loved the mashed potatoes 😊 complimented the steak very well!  Definitely recommend!
The food is really good. It's BYOB. The energy is amazing. Every time i have been there I've loved it.

Absolutely perfect! Great little diamond in the rough breakfast spot. Food is absolutely on point. Everything tasted fresh and well prepared. I couldn’t decide what to get because every time a plate passed by to a different table I changed my opinion. Will definitely be back
Good food. Service left us a little wanting.
The service was great and the food was so worth the wait! Telling all my friends about this little gem! Bring your own wine and enjoy time with your friends like we did.

Really lovely spot! Had alredy tried their delicious breakfast so decided to give dinner a try. OMG! Had the tropical salmon and it was DELICIOUS! It's not a fast food joint, so be prepared to wait, but know it is so worth it and they are super friendly. Breakfast, coffee and now Dinner all YUM!

I stopped by for Breakfast & there is a very warm & inviting atmosphere here. The staff is super friendly & the service was excellent! Get here early because the place fills up quick; it's easy to see why because the food is delicious! I recommend getting the Coquito French Toast!
A beautiful community, Mom & daughter run local restaurant in my neighborhood. The food is AMAZING and their customer service is beautiful to witness. I could not recommend this gem enough!
Guava pancakes and plantain frittata minus the sour cream were delicious.
Best breakfast/lunch place in Logan Square
Great food and delicious strong coffee! Servers are genuinley friendly. Great cozy neighborhood spot!

We got here about 1:30 and we didn’t realize you closed at 2 so we ended up asking for our food to go . I realized you forgot to put something I ordered in the bag so I went back it before I drove off and apparently wasn’t charged for the food that was ready to go . So I had to pay again . Next time let people know your about to close I didn’t even get salad dressing for my salad because you rushed us out . So disappointing and honestly upset that I even spent money here.

Very disappointed, we opened up our containers to enjoy our breakfast and just to find our meal is burnt!! Why would the cook let these pancakes leave out the kitchen to be served as a meal!!! These are not golden brown at all!! Its our first time trying food from this restaurant, not a good first impression!!!

We’ve been to Caribella twice in the last two weeks and have been so impressed! The food is amazing, they have a great custom coffee blend, and the service is laid back and polite. Their ingredients are so fresh and all of their dishes have big flavor. Give it a shot as your new brunch spot in Logan!
Coffee was so yummy, atmosphere was great for my bday brunch with the girls, and the food was unique and delicious!

Prepare to wait, not because this place is a long wait, but because the food is made to order and handled with care. This restaurant is BYOB, so the wait can easily be mitigated at low cost. The meals hit the spot. The ambiance is inviting, and my reservation was accommodated.

My husband and I came here for my 30th birthday breakfast feast. My expectations, as a Caribbean woman, were high.  I am happy to say that Caribella, exceeded my expectations. The food was incredible. The modern spin to Caribbean food is genius. The ingredients were fresh and the taste was, to say the least, an experience. I am happy to see my culture thrive in this industry. The service was humbling. I love that the Caribella has successfully married it's rooted culture with impeccable cuisine  Caribella is the spot . Wepa!!!
We arrived to a warm and friendly environment.  We ordered the vegetable skillet and chicken and waffles. The food was absolutely delicious. The service was outstanding.
Pricey, We were visiting so wont be back

We came to this restaurant because the last place had an hour and a half wait. I’m so glad we did. Breakfast was great, the service was lovely and the food came out timely. Coffee was on point too. I can definitely recommend this place . A place I can definitely recommend.
Delicious slightly tropical take on breakfast. Would for sure go back!
Love this place even more since they reopened. The coconut french toast is phenomenal. Service is great. Only wish they were open later.
Very nice place, nice friendly service and breakfast was great!

"Good vibe, good food, good people." -Zoroastrian's foody brother The Turkey sausage and bacon were particularly delicious. The guava pancake was new to me and tasted like something out of my mom's kitchen.
All I could say is WOW. Fantastic food, service, and friendly staff.
We enjoyed the breakfast lots a favorite Highly recommend the skillets

Not that surprised but not somewhere i will be back again. why? Not fond of the coffee, the minimal quantity of food delivered for the price, or the staff. I ordered 2 eggs, toast and coffee with steamed soy milk. This place has outstandingly high prices for this hood and it should be redesigned as a grab and go but slashing their prices in half. Our bill was almost 40 dollars and i was still starving. My fruit bowl probably had 1 strawberry, 1/4 of a kiwi and 3 grapes cut into small pieces so it looked like it was more. You want a side, well thats about 4$ and its coming straight from the frozen section in a store. Quality was ok but not enough for the price and not the type of ambience for a sit down. You won't get refills on the terribly bitter coffee, so why have a  server? Again, this place could probably be successful in its current location if they changed this to a grab and go, order up front and take out and then slash prices in 1/2. then it would be worth it.
Food was flavorful, fresh, and presented pretty. Service was helpful, nice and pleasant. Business was clean and looked well decorated. Will be returning again and recommending to friends to try.
The food here is really good! Recommend the coquito French toast!
Somehow, some of the best bacon I’ve ever had. Also anything with the vanilla rum syrup is worth your time.

Maybe this was an off day for them, but it took a long time to make 2 breakfast sandwiches and for 2 bacon-egg-cheese sandwiches, a cappuccino, and a coffee, was $28. The avocado I paid extra for was totally rotten, and even after I removed it, left a rotten taste. Bread was dry, everything else mediocre. I've had way better and faster $3 breakfast sandwiches from just about any corner deli.
Excellent service, lots of options, and fresh food. House blend coffee was above average. Worth a visit if you are in the area. BYOB is a nice option as well.
Patsy was a very nice server...
Nice people and great food

Great little restaurant.  Enjoyed a very healthy breakfast skillet that was served piping hot and delicious. It wasn't your typical greasy skillet...the veggies were cooked, yet.crisp, the cheese was light and the eggs were perfect.  The wait staff was very friendly. I'll go back!
Great food. Good people. Liked!
Wow! I just had one of the best steak sandwiches of my life here. They also sure know their way around a plantain. We'll definitely be back soon.

One of the best breakfast meals I’ve had in years, my family agrees. Everything was cooked to perfection with all fresh ingredients. Their pancakes are amazing!! Perfect combination of salty and sweet. I’m a vegetarian and personally recommend the egg sandwich with some extra vegetables and a smoothie to go with it. Atmosphere was lively and staff is very friendly. The restaurant used to be called Cafe Bella and served lunch and dinner but changed to Caribella as a breakfast and lunch service. Cute outside seating as well

Your new "go-to" neighborhood spot is here!  Place is awesome! Super cute and cozy vibe and a really cool and new fusion concept - better yet, they serve breakfast all day (ya baby!) AND IS BYOB! I got the Nutella Pancakes which, literally are my new favorite thing, ever! My wife got a smoothie which was reasonably priced and super refreshing.  I can't wait to try their lunch menu and FOR SURE will be back! Spread the word! This is the place!
Cooked an over easy egg over hard. Not a mistake I'd expect from a place that specializes in brunch.
Awesome food. Chill atmosphere.
Brilliant concept, delicious food.

This place is great. My gf and I stayed at an airbnb and went for a walk looking for breakfast. We found this place and it did not diappoint. The service is great, strong coffee and unique and tasty recipes. I recommend it for anyone visiting.
Amazing breakfast. Loved the French toast.
Love the food!!! Take a chance on this hidden gem ♡
Love it..small neighborhood restaurant..food was great..waitress was very attentive..being a rice snob...I was surprised at how good the rice tasted..definitely will be back..

Pancakes undercooked , not fluffy. Portions for breakfast sandwich are well measured but the chicken and waffles is really under served. The pic is half of the entree which costs $13. Other places have served actual fried chicken parts not jus strips. Chicken was great but really small portioned.

Had a great experience! The cafe/restaurant is a little tucked away, has a very homey feeling. The staff was wonderfully friendly. I had the avocado salad and all of the ingredients were very fresh and well-prepared. Can't reccommend this spot enough. Will be a regular from here on out.
Outstanding establishment. The food was incredible and the staff was very friendly

Do not hesitate, go and enjoy every bite at Caribella!  Best Cubano Sanwich I have ever had. The Chicken Avocado Salad had a full palate of flavors with every bite. The Coquito French Toast, especially the syrup with a touch of Rum was amazing.
Delicious food 😃
Great presentation and flavors
Omg simply delicious. If you are in a rush, this may not be for you.  However, if you are accustomed to Island life and the layed back life style.... when you travel.... it's worth the wait.

I used to visit Caribella when it was under the name Cafe Bella. After the completed renovation, I found a brand-new menu with all-day breakfast and lunch available. Though I was sad that some of my old favorites were gone, the server told me management was the same, so I knew the food would be fresh and well-made like before.  My Cubano with Spanish rice was flavorful, and I like how pulled pork was included in the sandwich. The lunch portion was generous, so I had leftovers to take home. The server was friendly and good with his pacing.  Everything is made to order, so don't expect the fastest wait times, but know that the wait is worth it! Glad to have a small business like this in my neighborhood.
